{"id": "ffe29416bae74294857bd2e321ef44c4", "timestamp": "2025-12-11 05:10:02", "name": "Scientist0", "content": "Thought: The team has converged on a conceptually rich and technically feasible direction that addresses a fundamental limitation in current LLMs: the lack of epistemic trajectory in multi-turn abstract discourse. By extending Dynamic Epistemic Framing with Normative Reasoning Graphs (NRGs), we shift the objective from static consistency to coherent, principled evolution of reasoning—mirroring human-like reflective equilibrium. This approach directly tackles the core challenge of enabling LLMs to engage authentically in philosophy and ethics, where stance development, tension management, and meta-reflective awareness are essential. The integration of attention-guided process tracing provides an empirically grounded method for constructing and validating NRGs, while adversarial debate benchmarks offer a rigorous evaluation framework. This topic is innovative, addresses a clear gap in current research, and has high potential impact in AI alignment, education, and ethical deliberation systems.\n\nTopic: ```json{\"Selected Topic\": \"Enabling Coherent Evolution of Reasoning in LLMs through Normative Reasoning Graphs for Multi-Turn Abstract Debate\"}```", "role": "assistant", "url": null, "metadata": null, "_colored_name": "\u001b[95mScientist0\u001b[0m"}
{"id": "feccf70285284d718dda4a5a616b2da8", "timestamp": "2025-12-11 05:10:06", "name": "Scientist0", "content": "The team has selected the topic: *\"Enabling Coherent Evolution of Reasoning in LLMs through Normative Reasoning Graphs for Multi-Turn Abstract Debate\"*, marking a shift from static consistency to dynamic, principled reasoning evolution in LLMs. This approach integrates **Dynamic Epistemic Framing** with **Normative Reasoning Graphs (NRGs)** to model stance development and reflective equilibrium in philosophical discourse. Key technical components include latent belief tracking, attention-guided process tracing, and dialogue-aware memory, supported by evaluation via adversarial debate benchmarks and expert annotation. The decision prioritizes empirical advancement over further theoretical discussion, enabling collaboration with domain experts and iterative refinement in real-world contexts.", "role": "assistant", "url": null, "metadata": null, "_colored_name": "\u001b[95mScientist0\u001b[0m"}
